author: Times Sports Staff
title: GIRLS SOCCER: Gananda clinches title
text:
GIRLS SOCCER: Gananda clinches title Times Sports Staff Finger Lakes Times | 0 comments 
WALWORTH — Gananda had to work until the final day of league play, but the Blue Panthers clinched its fifth consecutive Wayne County championship Thursday with a 3-0 victory over Sodus. 
Jenna Trabalzi, Giulia Mahoney (assist) and Jenna Ginsberg all found the net as the Blue Panthers capped off a 14-2 regular season, 11-1 in league play. Caroline White dished out two assists. 
Demetria Woodard (2 saves) and Bryanna Roos (1) split time in goal. 
Danielle Colasurdo turned aside eight shots for Sodus (10-6, 7-5). 
Marion 5, North Rose-Wolcott 1 
WOLCOTT — Chloe DeLyser (2 goals), Emma Means, Ashley Lange and Brianna Allen did the scoring for Marion (14-1-1). Danielle Stevens accumulated nine saves in goal. 
Kendall Huff tallied for the Cougars (4-12-1, 3-9) while Liz Lobrutto and Linsey Madison combined for 10 saves. 
NON-LEAGUE 
Marcus Whitman 5, Romulus 0 
GORHAM — Emily Thompson erupted for four goals and Audrey Prusinowski (assist) tacked on another to spark Marcus Whitman (5-11). Nichaela Commisso and Ellie Nemitz handed out assists; Katrina Meyer and Nemitz teamed up for six saves. 
Emma Voorhees compiled five saves for Romulus (1-14, 0-11).
